@node "Powersupply" "Powersupply"

    If you have a desktop or a tower AMIGA you can insert the card inside
    them. In this case, you don't need my powersupply.

    Put the card in a metalcase, that is the shield for the other
    components inside the computer and against them.

    Connect the shield to the analog ground (GND).

    The digital ground is the pin 7 of the serial port. Don't connect it to
    the analog ground (shield). There can be a difference up to 1,4 V.

    You can use the intern computer-power-supply for the card.

    +5 V   - normal red
    +12 V  - normal yellow
    -12 V  - normal blue
    ground - normal black   (analog ground for us)

    You MUST test this with a voltage proof tool.

    If you put the wrong voltage to the card it will die  -  certain !!!!
@endnode

@node "Settingtowork" "Setting to work"

    If the PCB is ready, connect all pins to out.(power, audio, MIDI,
    RESET, serialconnection).

    For the audio-output I use chinch-outputs.

